│ LCSSA formation, but later indvars uses the cached SCEV information incorrectly.\n\n3. Root Cause Analysis: The  │
│ root cause is in two places: First, in LCSSA.cpp line 194-195, when SE is available and the instruction has a    │
│ cached SCEV, LCSSA creates a new PHI and caches its SCEV. However, when SE is null (as in this case), this       │
│ caching doesn't happen properly. Second, in LoopUtils.cpp line 1556-1557, rewriteLoopExitValues assumes the loop │
